content: Today we will continue the topic that was opened by Ants, Tunnet and Andry, and we will review the world championship games.
Most of you have probably seen all the games,
but it is still interesting to analyse them, because you can also hear about the thoughts and tactics and emotions and all.
we start with small check first.

xinxin, Dragon, MIMI, tianxia, Liuchao, yyfcsd, comarck, xuwu, Joe1980cn, yysanyue, Iskander, pzh, skywalker, coco_yuang, mima, bergamot, Lithium, Samsone, Ikon, Renju_YinLC, lkogr, tommy, nu723, Timo, mayhem, YKS, hobbang, luwenzhe, xiaoxin, akira, Renju_liu_t, Whiz, Torsten, slamduk, sosei, benben, Shangjin, yaya, yboil, killer21st, yuelee00, ethereal, littlewhite, StarRain, cy, shuwang.
As you know, this World championship was very difficult for me.
Although I was emotionally in much better condition than last time,
I had been too busy with organizing of WC,
therefore I took a big risk,
that my home analyses were not sufficient.
yes, we all can see it
Before championship, I made realistic prognosis,
if all goes normally, I will get the top 3 place.
if unlucky, then outside of top 3.
but if things go well for me, and i have enough strength and some luck, then I may be 1st.
Those were my thoughts before games.
This time, there were so many strong players.
As you know, Sushkov nearly failed to enter the AT,
because he played some unlucky games in QT.
Fortunately, he was able to reach AT with 4 pts out of 7 from QT,
he's not in good shape at the beginning, maybe
with better coefficient than Aivo Oll
I was glad that he made it to AT.
without his participation, the AT would not be the same
Sushkov had been 2nd in AT twice before that - in 2001 and in 2003.
will be too easy for you then? :)
No, but I wanted to try my ability among best.
Now we will review my games,
and I will tell what happened there and why.
Because, the game records may have seemed weird for you. :))
so I would have to explain more.
my first game was with Tord Andersson,
My choice of opening followed the tactics,
that is to understand opponent first, and select the opening accordingly.
This 5th move may be poor choice for white in general,
but it was suitable against him,
Know yourself and know your opponent, you will win 100 out of 100  :P
if i let him into well known variant with black advantage,
then he could force at least draw.
Draw is not a good score against him, I thought.
If white doesnt play i6 now, then black wins at once.
Has anyone of you played this position before?
It is considered to be strong for black,
but one has to know all the best moves in order to reach there.
I had black and I couldn't win because of this 20
Andersson surprised me with this soft 27th move.
In the first look I thought it is a weak move,
but the more I spent time, the more I understood it was a wise move,
white has to solve 2 main tactical issues.

1. black has now strong power on both left and right side. How to eliminate both?
2. Eliminating both black powers is not enough, if white wants to win the game.
So I was puzzled and spent lots of time here.
After long thinking, i realized, it is not possible to overplay blacks with solid moves,
so i had to take the chance, and imitate some pseudo-activity
here black has a control at k8
i made him think that now the pair 24_26 was free to go,
and its very dangerous up there.
perhaps he could have tried something very aggressive,
he would  play safely in such critical moment.
where is white's next move? can you guess it?
there are 2 main questions - to attack on right up, or defend on left low.
so at least its clear that white has to defend.
I dont know how many defense moves are possible here,
but i had to consider one aspect while defending.
it is not enough just to defend here.
he will play his last move to up left, and offer a draw.
so i needed the plan which not only defends but helps me to gain tempo somehow
so i could go up right myself first
so I had to play a bit more aggressively than usual.
here g5. 2 of you guessed right
such a stone with a space around it,
else white will take control of that wing
he played the most logical moves,
indeed, the basic tactics of renju suggests f5,
and it happened to be best move indeed.
but its a bad move. why?
:) be brave to tell your thoughts, dear students
indeed, it is strongest for defense purpose - kills all black power.
But the downside is, it doesnt give any white potention.
black can exit this corner first
tempo needed i guess 40 is bad
which is not a good defense move,
but has some white potential in it.
now, it is not easy for black to exit the corner
black has a vcf threat now too
so I had to keep putting pressure on blacks below.
at the same time, trying not to lose the game :P
this looks like an imitation of the attack on 3x3,
but although it is possible to calculate, that black can escape from 3x3,
Didn't he has only a few time?
he desided to kill this lower corner "once and for all" with his strong powermove at e3,
hoping to continue in upper corner later.
but thats what i had anticipated with my moves 40 and 44.
black has win potential only together with the support of k5 area.
If black loses the k5 area support, then the e3 power alone is not enough for win.
And now, he was in difficult dilemma -
because white is getting strong on right lower area as well
not so pleasant situation for blacks
he spent time here, until got into time trouble.
His last hope was, that perhaps the diagonal connection between i2 and L5 would be strong enough to force white into defense.
I got my desired L12 finally :))
Only after that he realized how strong this upper corner was for whites.
until then he had thought that its easily defendable.
by the way, if you choose such tactics as white,
you take a lot of risk.
as you see, i had to be very brave, to make this L12,
Here he seeked the defense hopelessly,
I am sure, mr Okabe would not let me have win in this variant.
2nd round - I had to meet Andry Purk.

tianxia, Liuchao, skywalker, yyfcsd, Iskander, yboil, Samsone, Timo, MIMI, yaya, Ikon, benben, yysanyue, Lithium, nu723, hobbang, mima, pzh, Renju_YinLC, yuelee00, bergamot, Torsten, oddgod, littlewhite, akira, Joe1980cn, YKS, tommy, xuwu, comarck, Renju_liu_t, xinxin, shuwang, mayhem, Whiz, blueice, slamduk, xiaoxin, Shangjin, Cosmin, sosei, Dragon, cy, ethereal.
He was to open the game,
so I could bet with the probability of 99.999%, that he sets d11.
I kept white as I usually do,
Andry was in good condition because he beat me in the 1st game :P
since my game with Andersson ended sooner than Okabe-Purk,
so I could go to next room, and join the discussion of their game,
where people were standing in front of 5 meter wide screen,
My gane spend more than 5 hours, and youw game was less than 4 hours
and speaking of white attack chances.
the discussions were always so funny and interesting.
here in game, Andry was not sure which variant to play.
Maybe he heard it and won :(
he must have rabbit ears then
This is the "theory" of this 13th move.
do you all know these moves?
Tunnet, Aivo, Andry and Timo play these variants a lot, so they are very familiar with it.
it is not easy to say where is the best 21st move.
And I saw that you were in uneasy look
because I didnt have much experience in this variant,
so I had to create most of my tactics during the game.
I thought that you know Andry analyse it a lot and had abitity to get at least draw
And he beat Sushkov in QT, light?
before, in poland he had a game with tunnet,
it was in spring this year,
now there is no white win!!
not to use the four too early.
but that gives black chance to take i12 first.
I dont know if Andry was aware of white win or not,
but he remembered that I mentioned about i12 being the key question.
I needed a win in black advantage position.
similarly to first game with Andersson.
think about the strategy - white needs win
We(some Japanese) really admired your plan of this game, and I said 'why do I have to play against Ando??'
black can use initiative to kill all my potential
by this 26, i ensured that i have the potential on left, (e4), which cannot be killed by black's tempo-move.
such 27 would not force me to respond at all
but the stone at f7 supports black attack up left.
And now, I had to follow same tactics as against Andersson -
so I needed some aggressive stones
we will see really wondreful idea!
and before i can make second space move to e11,
which gives white potential so that black cannot exit that corner
, i must take care of black's power, rising from f9,
so i sacrificed my right wing material
just to eliminate the j13 power,
so that i could go e11 instead of f9,
which would give me 2 space stones, forcing black to stay in up corner and lose tempo.
the whole sceme was built on the idea of reaching white to e4 first.
It shows how this game was difficult and your moves were great
now, j13 is not longer a win threat.
he is trying to escape from corner,
i always defend with keeping white potential on up left
so he is trapped, he must respond!
hard work paid off - i got my e!!
so the stone at 48 is taking advantage of both left wing power, right wing potential, and j10 support.
so my stone at 32 was not only wasted for defense
who can show white win? say me
(those who didnt see game record, please)
you want to try once more?
How to say here I am here?

Shangjin, Ikon, xuwu, skywalker, Liuchao, Lithium, MIMI, yysanyue, tianxia, Samsone, oddgod, Iskander, yuelee00, yaya, Timo, xiaoxin, nu723, pzh, Torsten, bergamot, YKS, yboil, mayhem, hobbang, benben, Dragon, Joe1980cn, akira, yyfcsd, Whiz, cy, Renju_YinLC, littlewhite, comarck, ethereal, Renju_liu_t, xinxin, slamduk, mima, sosei, tommy, shuwang.
anyway, after 2 rounds, there were 3 people with 2 points - Taimla, Chingin and me.
But he became leader by the 6th round :P
whom you thought strongest opponent taimla or chingin?
they are all very tough opponents.
Mr Okabe is very strong too
Oh, he was in good condition too
as he told me after game - he was totally unable to fight for win.
draw was the only thing is his mind.
and for the first time maybe ever, he became a different person,
and played 100% on draw from the 1st move.
He got draw against Tunnet same way in the last WC
so he jumped into long variant.
Maybe he didnt want positional fight,
because I had done quite well in first 2 games
nice filling style, famous draw pattern.
i want to hear if you know the moves in most famous d11 variant.
but on another table, the game Tarannikov-Andersson took place.
but Andersson didnt know where to put 34.
tarannikov spent all his time here
and could not find any good plan for black
so their game went on like that...
and white had a tempo-catcher move at g13
It seems that Andersson really like gambling :) And Tarannikov really like to make draw :P
so Tarannikov must have hated this 34
there has not been any serious analysing.
It will be a big question of this varient
hmm, i know my home analyzing today :)
my quick analyse found such response:
but then i found a continuation for white.
so there will be the fight over tempo in upper corner now.
if black wins that fight, then black advantage and probably draw,
if white wins the upper corner tempo battle,
then white gets e4 and the advantage on the bottom
i want to be white now :)
so both black and white have material,
i tried so hard to win..
i had to consider different aspects of the position.
i cannot just develop on lower right now.
because of absence of e12 control.
without e12 control. black may win below.
but if white doesnt have that upper threat,
then black has win potential in the bottom
so i had to keep that in mind at all times.
I am sorry. I will behave.
now i had eliminated the lower danger,
and same time attacking upper area through e12
i wished my 58 were at c10 instead,
because then he cannot take e13,
and i could exit upper wing with tempo
i had this one played too
so i played a half-defense move
but it cost me 1 useful line
it was now too late to hope to win in right lower corner
so i tried my last chance up there.
as you see, black has tons of material,
and create my own lines in the middle of his potential,
black is getting stronger by that
but i still had my hopes on win.
Oh, I will fix this game in WC web site now, 66 and 75 was wrong
if not, i am in trouble :)
o9 enough + chance to win some more space
if we have many choices for defense,
then we choose the one which is most useful for later purposes outside that corner.
this 86 is the only stone which is defensive enough, and also has some support for lower corner.
it was pity to lose half point here.
but i was not prepared for this tactics.
i was so sure he would fight for win, and expected all kinds of variants,
but he surprised me, by forcing a draw.
It means, next time, if I want to win against him, i have to keep his draw strategy in mind too.
These were the first 3 games of WC.
Next Tuesday, we will continue from here.
thank you all for coming. see you next week!
